    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-06-17T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-06-17T19:00:00-05:00" n="153"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d153">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/6–1847: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Mukden</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ward</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mukden</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-06-18T09:00:00+09:00"
                            >June 18, 1947—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 18—6:56 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>98. Tempo fighting Ssupingkai has subsided. Nationals not only control city but
                    have made small counterdrives outside city, recapturing airport which has
                    changed hands several times past few days. Source NECC to Consulate interpreter.
                    Very noticeable air of optimism among Chinese over military situation in
                    distinct contrast to obvious depressed attitude 10 days ago. Majority Chinese
                    contacted feel outcome engagements Ssupingkai will largely determine course of
                    events this area next 6 months. National reinforcements have arrived in
                    Manchuria. Ninety-second Army, formerly Hopei province, landed at Chinwangtao.
                    Source NECC to Consulate interpreter.</p>
                <p>Sent Embassy as 174, repeated Dept as 8 [<hi rend="italic">98</hi>], Changchun as
                    74.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ward</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
